The time for firing dried roof tiles is about 1.5 time longer than for bricks, according to (Weibel &amp; Stritz (1995)). An expert of the clay production industry is very sceptical concerning this factor. He says that in nowadays tiles are burned in fast firing furnaces. As no better data are available nevertheless this factor has in general been used to increase the energy consumption and emission rates for brick production in order to adapt the values to tile production. 

