      <intermediateExchange id="61a6e11e-d54b-5327-bb19-a80a99446497" unitId="de5b3c87-0e35-4fb0-9765-4f3ba34c99e5" casNumber="8006-14-2" amount="0.00033023188123024275" sourceId="13c07be7-5ae6-4105-8a2c-e63dfaf0e107" sourceYear="1996" sourceFirstAuthor="Bruck, M." intermediateExchangeId="a9007f10-7e39-4d50-8f4a-d6d03ce3d673" activityLinkId="2d14c7b2-0cbb-5501-91d6-d44eaf915744">
        <name xml:lang="en">natural gas, high pressure</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">m3</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Estimation, based on literature values. Natural gas and propan are used as combustible. It is assumed that the data is "net calorific value" with an efficiency of 0.87.
The time for firing dried roof tiles is about 1.5 time longer than for bricks, according to (Weibel &amp; Stritz (1995)). An expert of the clay production industry is very sceptical concerning this factor. He says that in nowadays tiles are burned in fast firing furnaces. As no better data are available nevertheless this factor has in general been used to increase the energy consumption and emission rates for brick production in order to adapt the values to tile production. 

Further references:
Weibel T. and Stritz A. (1995) Ökoinventare und Wirkungsbilanzen von Baumaterialien; Grundlagen für den ökologischen Vergleich von Hochbaukonstruktionen. In: ESU-Reihe Nr. 1/95. Laboratorium für Energiesysteme, Eidg. Technische Hochschule (ETH), Zürich.

Frischknecht R., Jungbluth N., Althaus H.-J., Doka G., Dones R., Hellweg S., Hischier R., Humbert S., Margni M., Nemecek T. and Spielmann M. (2007) Implementation of Life Cycle Impact Assessment Methods. Final report ecoinvent Data v2.0 No. 3. Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, CH, Online-Version under: www.ecoinvent.ch &lt;http://www.ecoinvent.ch&gt;.
EcoSpold01Location=RER</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.00033023188123024275" mu="-8.01571547986633" variance="0.05" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.1461"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="5" completeness="5" temporalCorrelation="5" geographicalCorrelation="3" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="3"/>
          <comment xml:lang="en">;</comment>
        </uncertainty>
        <property propertyId="f2283db2-62e4-467f-b9ac-c4f45be563b4" amount="0.5059999999999997" isDefiningValue="false" isCalculatedAmount="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
