      <elementaryExchange id="86aa5301-71bd-5344-a235-71d2a21e9c29" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" amount="0.000115" sourceId="13c07be7-5ae6-4105-8a2c-e63dfaf0e107" sourceYear="1996" sourceFirstAuthor="Bruck, M." elementaryExchangeId="d3260d0e-8203-4cbb-a45a-6a13131a5108">
        <name xml:lang="en">NMVOC, non-methane volatile organic compounds</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Estimation, based on literature values. Total measured emissions within the system boundaries. It is assumed that an average NMVOC includes about 80% weight of C.
A corresponding probing by an expert of the clay production industry has shown that the factor of 1.5 for CO2, CO, dust, NO2, SO2, and org. C is realistic (between 0.3 and 1.7). The source is based on the composition of the raw material clay which differs from the raw material which is used for brick.

Further references:
Weibel T. and Stritz A. (1995) Ökoinventare und Wirkungsbilanzen von Baumaterialien; Grundlagen für den ökologischen Vergleich von Hochbaukonstruktionen. In: ESU-Reihe Nr. 1/95. Laboratorium für Energiesysteme, Eidg. Technische Hochschule (ETH), Zürich.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.000115" mu="-9.070578429601024" variance="0.17" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.2661"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="5" completeness="5" temporalCorrelation="5" geographicalCorrelation="3" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="3"/>
          <comment xml:lang="en">;</comment>
        </uncertainty>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">NMVOC</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">non-methane volatile organic compounds</synonym>
