          <comment xml:lang="en">The ratio C fossil/C biogenic has been estimated to 50:50 using data concerning global material uses and mass flows (J.K. Steinberger et al., Ecological Economics, 2010, 69:1148–1158). Repartition of different fossil fuels was estimated using production volumes in ecoinvent v3.)
The following list of representative NMVOC were considered following EEA definitions: benzene, xylene, propane, butane, and ethane
The ratio C fossil/C biogenic has been estimated to 50:50 using data concerning global material uses and mass flows (J.K. Steinberger et al., Ecological Economics, 2010, 69:1148–1158). Repartition of different fossil fuels was estimated using production volumes in ecoinvent v3.)</comment>
        </property>
